The Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU), University of Ibadan chapter, said on Tuesday none of its members was involved in examination malpractices at the institution’s Distance Learning Centers (DLC). <img class="alignnone  wp-image-1266637" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=539%2C302&#038;ssl=1" alt="ASUU threatens showdown over IPPIS" width="539" height="302" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=768%2C430&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=1024%2C573&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=58%2C32&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?resize=560%2C314&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ASSU-1.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 539px) 100vw, 539px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Chairman of ASUU at the institution, Prof. Deji Omole, said contrary to earlier reports, the suspects arrested and being quizzed by the Department of State Services (DSS) in connection with the exam fraud were non-academic staff in the DLC technical unit. Omole noted that seven non-academic staff of the DLC were picked up by the DSS last Thursday for allegedly aiding and abetting examination malpractices and compromising the integrity of examinations. He insisted that academic staff had not been fingered or linked to the fraud an